<body>
    @Html.Partial("_HeaderPage")
    <div class="main" style=" margin-top: 40px; margin-bottom: 20px;">
        <div class="container" style="padding-right: 10px; padding-left: 10px;">
            <header class="header">
                <div>
                    <div class="post-detail" style="display: grid;">
                        <strong style="font-size:28px;">UNDERGRADUATE PROGRAM -INTERNATIONAL BUSINESS </strong>
                        <hr style="width: 780px; height: 3px; background-color: #dcb42a; display: inline-block; margin: 0 0 15px; border: none;border-radius: 10px;">
                    </div>
                </div>
            </header>
            <div class="content">
                <strong>INTRODUCTION</strong>
                <p>International Business programme was issued according to Decision No. 146/QĐ-ĐT dated January 14, 2010 by the President of StuM and assigned to the StuM University according to Decision 
                No. 723/QĐ-ĐT dated March 1, 2010 of the President of StuM. The program was approved by StuM as a high-quality training program corresponding to school’s specificity according to Decision No. 3345/QĐ-StuM 
                dated October 24, 2016. As of December 2017, the program has trained 7 courses with a total of 1059 students, of which 307 have graduated. The graduation rate with ranks of Credit and Distinction is 84%.
                </p>
                <img class="img-fluid" src="~/Content/img/StuM (13).png"/>
                <p>According to the recent result of a quality assessment by an independent agency, the International Business program is highly appreciated for its quality program including content, teaching team, management 
                team, teaching-learning organization, testing… The alumni highly appreciated the quality and practicality of the program. The International Business students also impress the recruiters with the English proficiency,
                professionalism, and adaptability to work and working environment.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    @Html.Partial("_FooterPage")
